<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="217" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,760,1642,2081]" pageId="10" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,245,1866,1889]" pageId="10" pageNumber="217">Biology.</emphasis>
The species has been seen on jasmine plants, 
<emphasis box="[151,311,1899,1922]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="217">Tecoma stans</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis box="[383,612,1899,1922]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="217">Butea monosperma</emphasis>
, where it is associated with thrips (
<bibRefCitation author="DEVI &amp; GUPTA" box="[410,636,1930,1953]" firstAuthor="DEVI" pageId="10" pageNumber="217" pagination="313 - 320" refId="ref17691" refString="DEVI N. &amp; GUPTA P. R. 2010: Anthocorid bugs encountered on cultivated crops and ornamentals, and an attempt to rear Orius niger Wolff under laboratory conditions. Pest Management and Economic Zoology 18: 313 - 320." type="journal article" year="2010">DEVI &amp; GUPTA 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="BALLAL &amp; YAMADA" firstAuthor="BALLAL" pageId="10" pageNumber="217" pagination="329 - 366" refId="ref16480" refString="BALLAL C. R. &amp; YAMADA K. 2016: Anthocorid predators. Pp. 329 - 366. In: OMKAR (eds): Ecofriendly pest management for food security. Elsevier, London, 727 pp." type="book chapter" year="2016">BALLAL &amp; YAMADA 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In the Palearctic Region, this species is well known as a predator of aphids, thrips, and eggs of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,283,2026,2049]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
, pentatomids, and mites (
<bibRefCitation author="CARAYON &amp; STEFFAN" firstAuthor="CARAYON" pageId="10" pageNumber="217" pagination="53 - 63" refId="ref17138" refString="CARAYON J. &amp; STEFFAN J. R. 1959: Observations sur le regime alimentaire des Orius et particulierement, d'Orius pallidicornis (Reuter) (Heteroptera: Anthocoridae). Cahiers des Naturalistes, Bulletin des Naturalistes Parisiens, Nouvelle Serie 15: 53 - 63." type="journal article" year="1959">CARAYON &amp; STEFFAN 1959</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="PERICART" box="[219,381,2058,2081]" firstAuthor="PERICART" pageId="10" pageNumber="217" refId="ref20308" refString="PERICART J. 1972: Hemipteres Anthocoridae, Cimicidae, Microphysidae de l'Ouest-Palearctique. Faune de l'Europe et du bassin Mediterraneen. Vol. 7. Masson et Cie Editeurs, Paris, 402 pp." type="book" year="1972">PÉRICART 1972</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
